==Arabic==
===Etymology===
From {{ARchar|[[بيت]]}} (house) and {{ARchar|[[مقدس]]}} (holy, sacred).

===Noun===
{{ARchar|'''بيت المقدس'''}} (Beyt al-Muqáddas)

# [[Jerusalem]] (the capital of [[Palestine]] and [[Israel]])

====Synonyms====
*{{ARchar|[[القدس]]}} (al-Quds)
*{{ARchar|[[أورشليم]]}} (Ūrušalīm)

